{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to this wavefront-shaping based wave control for coherent focusing, we also consider the possibility of controlling both the input wavefront and the metasurface configuration to maximize the deposited energy.",
    "To that end, we use the physical model to select a metasurface configuration out of the 10 5 configurations from the training data set that we expect to yield the largest deposited energy.",
    "Even though these configurations were part of the calibration data, because the training data was phaseless in the case of Fig. 3e and lacked one relevant transmission coefficient in the case of Fig.",
    "S2a, our ability to identify a metasurface configuration that maximizes the deposited energy is remarkable.",
    "Our dictionary-search-based inverse-design algorithm consists in (i) establishing the dictionary by running the physics-based forward model for the 10 5 configurations, (ii) evaluating the cost function (focused intensity) for each dictionary entry, and (iii) selecting the dictionary entry with the best cost function."
  ]
}